headline: Britain's Kainos jumps on upbeat annual outlook
summary: Kainos, a partner of U.S. software firm Workday, said its Workday products division — which builds applications used within the platform — continued to grow and passed the $100 million annual recurring revenue milestone in July.  Kainos said momentum was picking up across its divisions, with new projects prompting it to hire more staff and make greater short-term use of contractors.
